name: Umami by Han Amsterdam
description:
Oriental Bar & Kitchen UMAMI by Han Amsterdam is a modern all-day concept where guests can choose for a quick lunch, lovely Asian finger-food or an extensive 3 course menu with 6 sharing-dishes per person.
The fresh ingredients, light dishes, wide variety of wines and tea-pairing are a great match with the health-consciousness of chef Han Ji.

We weren't very large party, so a lot of folks ordered a LOT of different things, but for myself and my husband, we ordered the gyoza, the shrimp buns, I ordered the seafood ramen, he ordered the salmon hot stone rice dish. Even my 7 month old appreciated the lobster broth in the ramen, and the drinks were absolutely amazing as well.

name: Pacific Amsterdam
description: Eten, drinken en dansen: het kan allemaal bij Pacific, de all-day hotspot met een groot en zonnig terras gelegen in het Westerpark. Van 's ochtends vroeg tot diep in de nacht kun je terecht bij deze iconische plek op de Westergas. Koffie of lunch, casual dining, een biertje in de zon of dansen tot in de vroege uurtjes: Pacific heeft het allemaal!

name: Hannah's
description:
Hannah's is een horeca zaak in Amsterdam West, waar La Dolce Vita hoog in het vaandel staat! Een unieke plek waar je komt ontbijten, lunchen, een lekker koffietje komt drinken en aan het einde van de week (donderdag, vrijdag en zaterdag) gezellig komt borrelen of dineren.

Een Sociaal Initiatief
Daarnaast is Hannah's een dagbesteding plek waar ons team voor een deel bestaat uit mensen met "mental different abilities". Bij Hannah's doet iedereen mee! Dit betekent dat jouw koffie, lunch, aperitivo of dinner met extra liefde, zorg en aandacht geserveerd wordt.

The first time was a pleasant experience, but unfortunately, they have really gone down in quality. It was very busy, and there was only one waitress, who clearly had too much on her plate. She was very sweet and helpful, but unable to manage the whole floor by herself.

We ordered an omelette on sourdough and grilled vegetables and a focaccia with cheese, artichoke, and a chestnut-mushroom mix.

It took an hour and 15 minutes from the moment we came in until our food came. The omelette was nice, but the grilled vegetables were mushy and the toast was burnt. The focaccia had whole artichokes on it which was a bit much, and the chestnut-mushroom mixture was just straight up missing.

For what you get, it is also just too expensive now. The previous time (same prices but higher quality) it was worth the price.

They are nice people so I do not have the heart to give 2 stars even though my experience was certainly not worth more than that. But I really hope they bounce back. name: La Casa Di Michael
description: Italie is dichterbij dan u denkt, La Casa di Michael is hier een goed voorbeeld van. Proef het echte Italie en kom dineren in een mediterrane en levendige sfeer. Er is een ruime keuze aan authentieke Italiaanse specialiteiten maar ook de traditionele pizza's en pasta's ontbreken niet op de menukaart. De zonnige, zuidelijke inrichting en de vriendelijke bediening zorgen voor een geslaagde Italiaanse avond. Als de Nederlandse temperatuur mee wil werken aan de Italiaanse omstandigheden kunt u ook buiten op ons terras genieten. Proef het echte Italie met zijn zon, cultuur en culinaire veelzijdigheden, bij La Casa di Michael zijn alle ingredienten hiervoor aanwezig!

The menu offers a great selection of food, with French bistro-inspired options that are both satisfying and well-executed.

We started with the artichoke and prawn croquettes, which were a wonderful balance of flavors and textures, setting the tone for the rest of the meal. For mains, we had the beef, cod, pea ravioli, and steak tartare. Each dish was beautifully presented, showcasing fresh ingredients and classic techniques. The simplicity of the food allows the quality to really shine.

The venue itself is truly something special. Housed in an old water pumping factory, the restaurant's high ceilings and preserved factory equipment give it a striking industrial-chic vibe. Dining here feels like being part of a unique blend of history and modern style, making the atmosphere just as memorable as the food.

name: Bar Lusconi - Cucina Italiana | Italiaans Restaurant Amsterdam
description: BAR.LUSCONI brengt een stukje Italie naar het hart van Amsterdam-West. Bij ons geniet je van heerlijke pizza's, authentieke Italiaanse gerechten, smaakvolle antipasti en verfrissende drankjes, allemaal bereid met hoogwaardige ingredienten. Of je nu langskomt voor een ontspannen lunch, een gezellig diner, of een bedrijfsborrel, BAR.LUSCONI biedt de ideale sfeer voor elke gelegenheid. Onze menukaart combineert traditionele Italiaanse smaken met een moderne twist. Bezoek ons op het Mercatorplein in de Baarsjes en ervaar de unieke Italiaanse sfeer!

description: Met Restaurant, heeft een geweldige sfeer. Populair bij de lokale bevolking, studenten, toeristen en professionals van jong tot oud. We ordered the bok choy salad, mushroom risotto, and veal cheeks. Although we joined the dining quite late, and only one chef was actively working--leaving us with a considerable wait--every dish was worth it, exceeding our expectations and leaving us wanting more.

The bok choy salad was refreshing, with a truly unique flavor profile brought together by the crispy chips and the crunch of the bok choy. The mushroom risotto was creamy, bursting with flavor, and perfectly executed with a delicate texture that made it nearly impossible not to take another bite. The veal cheeks were outstanding, with incredible texture and flavor, though the potato on the side felt slightly confusing.

We spoke to the server about the chef and learned that he is Italian, drawing inspiration from American and other European cuisines.

While the service was slow due to the single chef in the kitchen, we didn't mind, as the quality of the food made up for the wait. name: Benji's West
description: Benji's West is a cozy Amsterdam restaurant where people can escape from the high-paced city life and find themselves in a peaceful, green oasis combined with an urban feel. During the day, one can enjoy a brunch (lunch & breakfast) menu with a large variety of dishes inspired by cultures and cuisines from all over the world with a tropical twist. Our drink menu consists of excellent coffee from the local roastery LOT61, as well as fresh juices, smoothies, and our cocktail bar serves the best brunch cocktails in Amsterdam. Visit our cozy cafe at Baarsjesweg 188, Amsterdam West and experience the unique vibe yourself.

The woman who waited on us (Lydia?) was lovely, very friendly and helpful with our order. They have good coffee, offered mimosas and other beverages, and a great selection of Dutch pancakes. We had one pancake with apples and bacon, managing perfectly our request to go easy on the cheese. My pancake was ham and caramelized onions with the standard amount of cheese on top. Let me tell you... they were both FABULOUS!! Much thinner than other pancakes we've had in Amsterdam, more like a crepe than a pancake, and the pancakes were executed perfectly with the right amount of ingredients in each. Both combinations were incredible and a little syrup on the one with apples & bacon had our eyes rolling back in our heads (I'm salivating writing this review)! Thank you for taking the time to share your feedback. We sincerely apologise that your recent visit did not live up to your expectations, especially after having such a great experience with us in the past. We strive to deliver exceptional service and a comfortable environment for all of our guests, and it's clear we fell short this time.

While we were hopeful the rain wouldn't arrive until later, the weather took an unexpected turn, which unfortunately impacted the overall experience. However, we understand that weather should never be an excuse for disorganisation, loud music, or a space that doesn't suit our guests.

We would love the opportunity to make it up to you with a complimentary meal and a much-improved experience. Please send us an email at hello@boothuis.amsterdam so that we can personally arrange something for you.

Thank you again for your feedback, and we hope to welcome you back soon under much better circumstances.

Kind regards,

name: VESSEL
description:
WELCOME AT VESSEL

Vessel is a place where people come together. It's a vibrant hangout to get cosy around the fireplace during those cold days, and a local beach in the summer with an amazing view overlooking the IJ. All year round, Vessel is your all-day destination to eat, enjoy and share delicious dishes.

Come by, escape the hectic city buzz to relax and meet like-minded people in a dynamic, lively atmosphere.

[{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNmdE1MWVVnEAE","rating":null,"name":"New---reviewer13","reviewer_profile":"https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g188590-d20410825-r985669314?m=68573&staydates=2025_01_26_2025_01_27&uguests=1_2_0&supdv=unknown&supuc=NL&supul=en","review_text":"Having previously stayed at Westervilla in Dec '23 where we had an amazing time, we returned in Dec '24  along with 2 of our friends, with high expectations.||Sadly, our expectations were dashed soon after arriving.||As we checked in, we realised the restaurant (which previously was a chilled and intimate, but subsequently has had a rebrand since we last visited) was busy with very large (and loud) Christmas party groups. ||We weren't warned at all in advance of arriving, and when we questioned also found out there was to be music playing for the party too.||Less than impressed, we had no choice but to chance it and stay as it was too late to cancel and rebook something else. |On our first night of 3 (Friday night) we had extremely loud thumping music underneath us until 1am.|When we spoke to the staff, they couldn't have cared less and just offered ear plugs. Also, when we enquired about speaking to the manager we were told 'he's not here, just email'. No offer of any resolution or promise to get the manager to contact us.||The following day we enquired if we were to experience the same hellish noise as we had on the Friday night. ||We were assured that there were no full parties on the Saturday night, and that the music would stop by 11pm. We once again enquired about talking to the manager and were once again rebuffed with 'email'.||Sadly, our Saturday night experience was just as poor, although no parties as such, thumping music resonated through the floor of our room, well past the promised 11pm.|I went down at 11;25pm where I was told the music would stop in 5 minutes.|The music DID stop, but what DIDN'T stop was over an hour of scraping and banging furniture, shouting staff, slamming doors, all this after two nights of complaints about noise from 50% of their entire guests that weekend!||We once again emailed (having not had any response to our original emails so far)||On the Sunday, we finally had contact via phone from the Manager, Mario.||I'd like to credit him with trying to resolve the situation. We sat down at the restaurant below the rooms where our group of 5  (spread over 3 rooms) spoke to him. He understood our frustrations, and was frustrated at his staff's lack of compassion, driving us to email, and for not further raising our issued with him.||He said that he would like to offer us a free meal that night, and the owner, Christian would refund one night of our stay.||We explained that after two nights of completely disturbed sleep, that we were fully expecting two nights to be refunded. |Mario said he would go back to the owner and make our case, and agreed it was a reasonable request.|We did enjoy a complimentary meal we were offered on the Sunday night, but of course that really isn't a huge cost to the hotel/restaurant at cost price.||Sadly, on our last day after we had checked out, Mario called to say Christian, the owner would not budge on our request for a refund on the two nights.||We explained our disappointment but of course had no choice but to accept the refund of one night, we did explain that when asked to review the hotel, we could only be fully honest about our experience, and lack of satisfactory resolution.||It is such a shame that after an amazing experience 12 months before, that we would now never return to Westervilla. The staff (other than Mario) really couldn't have cared less about our discomfort, and the owner didn't care enough to offer us the compensation we clearly should have been offered.||I have never ever written this before, but I would advise people to avoid staying there as a hotel guest.||We are back in Amsterdam in July for a concert, and Westervilla should have been our natural choice, we will now take our custom to a hotel where our custom is fully valued.","published_at":"3 weeks ago","published_at_date":"2024-12-22T23:59:59","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":[]},{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNYMHVMa2ZnEAE","rating":5,"name":"Ellie Lancaster","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106282298519911563733?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Stayed at the Westervilla Hotel for 2 nights with my partner, and had an amazing time. name: Karavaan
description:
Vanaf vroeg in de ochtend kun je langs onze Koffiebar op de hoek voor jouw koffie (to-go) en croissantje.
Het centrale deel van Karavaan biedt genoeg ruimte om te kunnen werken, uitgebreid te lunchen en dit alles over te laten gaan in een borrel / diner. De avonden staan in het teken van eten, borrelen, heel veel speciaal bier, cocktails en lekkere wijnen, met de enorme centrale bar als bruisend middelpunt. Op de kaart vind je gerechten uit de diverse gebieden van de Karavaan route.

description: Kazik - the living room of Cracow in the Centre of Amsterdam. Authentic, home-made, Polish comfort food that will trigger your palate and soul. The simple concept of Polish snacks & vegan lunch options combined with traditional cakes and high quality coffee.

I especially loved the pierogi and the "Meat Lovers" zapiekanka. We'll probably come back soon.

The only thing I wouldn't recommend is the orange cheesecake. While the base of the cheesecake was really good, the orange topping was overwhelmingly bitter. Next time, I'll try a different flavor.

Suggestions for Improvement:
1.	Waiting List and Time Limit: The place is small and has limited seating. It was chaotic trying to find a spot to sit and eat, especially with some people staying at tables without ordering. A waiting list system and a time limit for tables could help manage this better.
2.	Add a Cooker Hood: The smell from the cooking was noticeable throughout the space. Installing a range hood would help with ventilation and improve the dining experience.
3.	Staff Training and Process Optimization: The staff could use better training, and the service processes could be more organized to improve efficiency and customer experience.
4.	Install a Door Closer: The door was often left open, and with freezing temperatures outside, this made things uncomfortable. name: Cantine de Caron
description: Cantine de Caron, is het grootste restauarant van de familie Caron. Gelegen midden in het hart van het historische Westerpark. In het industriele decor van dit voormalige fabrieksgebouw geniet je van klassieke Franse gerechten met een mediterraan accent, omringd door de levendigheid van het Westergasterrein. Neem plaats binnen in de warme, rauwe ambiance van het monumentale pand of op ons zonnige terras met uitzicht op het park. Of je nu op zoek bent naar een gezellige lunch in de buurt of een uitgebreid diner, bij Cantine de Caron ben je altijd welkom.

name: Franggo West
description:
Rooted on the African islands of Cape Verde where our grandfather was born, our family spread all along Portugal. We as a father and daughter moved to Amsterdam where we decided to start our experience into our concept of Franggo.

At Franggo we serve authentic Portuguese Flame Grilled Chicken influenced by african touches. We believe in transforming this original product to modern times with urban vibes. Our core values are to serve the best chicken fast, in a cool ambiance, offering the best prices. By doing so Franggo is one big happy family.

name: Le French Cafe - Admiraal de Ruijterweg
description: La Brasserie - Admiraal de Ruijterweg 1, Amsterdam. Het restaurant belooft de typische bruisende, Franse brasserie-ervaring, maar dan voorzien van wat onvervalste Mokumse bravoure. Hier kunnen buurtbewoners, foodies en liefhebbers van de moderne Franse keuken terecht voor een relaxte sfeer en uitgebreide menukaart vol gerechten met een ietwat funky touch. En - ook niet geheel onbelangrijk - neerploffen op een heerlijk, zonnig terras met uitzicht op de gracht.

name: Rangla Punjab
description: Rangla Punjab, een nieuw Indiaas pareltje in de culinaire wereld, biedt een authentieke ervaring met chefs die meer dan 20 jaar expertise delen. Deze culinaire meesters brengen unieke smaken tot leven, zoals de zeldzame Tandoori Soya Malai Chaap, naast klassiekers zoals Butter Chicken en Chicken Tikka Masala. Bij Rangla Punjab staat diversiteit voorop, met een ruime keuze aan vegetarische opties en de garantie dat alle gerechten halal zijn. Elke maaltijd is afgestemd op uw voorkeur: kies uit mild, medium of spicy. Gelegen bij een tramhalte, is Rangla Punjab gemakkelijk toegankelijk en klaar om uw smaakpapillen te verwennen met zijn rijke, authentieke Indiase keuken. Een niet te missen bestemming voor liefhebbers van de Indiase keuken!

The restaurant was full, and despite an issue with our booking, they managed to find space and set up a table for two.
The food was excellent. We started with the burrata and the Jerusalem artichoke, followed by the aubergine and the cod with broccolini. We finished with the pear. Everything was delicious, but a special mention goes to the sauces--the one paired with the burrata was particularly outstanding.
However, during dinner, they decided to dim the lights almost completely. While the atmosphere was already subdued, this was a bit too much for our taste. Without the candle placed very close to us, it was hard to see what was on our plates. That was the only negative aspect.
Aside from that, the staff were incredibly friendly, and the dishes were excellent. I would definitely recommend this restaurant.","published_at":"4 weeks ago","published_at_date":"2024-12-14T22:24:04","response_from_owner_text":"Hey Venceslas ,

Went to their website directly from google maps. There we can just use direct booking.

After arrival, the weather was nice that i decided to move outdoor. The arrangement was easy and hassle free. Waiter was understanding and accommodating.

The dutch would call this place gezellig. I do agree with one commenter that the distance between one desk to another a little bit close by. If it is a bit busy, it would difficult to talk with friends. Luckily i was there on Sunday evening and it was not as crowded.

Now let's get to food. I loved the Burrata. Light but definitely packed with flavors. The burrata itself was exceptional, but melon was standard. Second menu i took was Mackerel. Sauce was good, fish was properly cooked! Personally think the fish can be improved. If there is a way to increase the freshness of it would be greatly appreciated.

As for Cote de beouf, it was indeed good! For the price and also the quality, it was within expectations.

name: Baires Empanadas & Pasteleria

name: Parsa Persian Restaurant
description:
Bij Bar & Grill Restaurant Parsa bent u van harte welkom voor ontbijt, lunch of diner. U geniet van heerlijke Perzische gerechten.

Bar & Grill Restaurant Parsa is te vinden aan de Clercqstraat 2 Amsterdam waarin, Perzische oudheid voor een belangrijk deel het interieur zijn gezellige sfeer geeft. Binnen bieden wij een ruime aantal zitplaatsen aan.

Als 't u verheugt om in een gezellige en ongedwongen sfeer 'n avondje te genieten van heerlijke Iraanse gerechten die volgens Perzische traditie vakkundig worden bereid, bezoek ons dan eens in ons Iraanse Bar & Grill Restaurant in Amsterdam.

Tevens serveren wij ook traditionele Italiaanse gerechten. Kom gerust langs voor een heerlijke pasta of maak een keuze uit veel verschillende pizza's.

Northern Italy. Our menu features high-quality ingredients, crafted into dishes
that go beyond the usual Italian menu, reflecting the rich culinary traditions of
our unique region. Our takeaway packaging ensures that every dish preserves its
full flavor and arrives at your table as delicious as it was meant to be.

My friend and I stopped by for brunch on the weekend and sat outside, just around the corner of the bustling shopping street Jan Evertsenstraat. A great place for people watching!
The staff were super friendly and accommodating, albeit a bit slow at first to take our orders and bring us drinks. But service picked up as the place got busier.
My friend had the smoked salmon sandwich and I opted for the eggs. The salmon was lovely and fresh, and my eggs were poached to perfection and finished with yogurt and spices - absolutely delicious! Coffees were great and my friend also ordered some refreshing homemade passionfruit lemonade.
During the day this is a superb place to chill out, have a meal or just meet for coffee. At night, it turns into a bar, and besides beer and cocktails apparently there are also all kinds of activities (like pub quizzes, performances and speed dating). Highly recommended and we will definitely be back for more!","published_at":"3 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-09-20T15:42:46","response_from_owner_text":"Beste B B,

Kate

name: Funky Thai | Restaurant in Amsterdam
description:
Welcome to Funky Thai, an authentic Thai restaurant in Amsterdam at Kinkerstraat 178, offering a unique culinary journey. Immerse yourself in exotic Thai flavors in a charming setting where each dish is meticulously prepared by our skilled chefs.
A must-visit for Asian cuisine enthusiasts in Amsterdam, Funky Thai guarantees a delightful burst of flavors in every dish.
Conveniently located at Kinkerstraat 178, our restaurant invites you to savor the magic of Thai cuisine in Amsterdam. Join us for an unforgettable experience, and let the best of Thailand's flavors captivate your senses.

The food was excellent and offered a delightful change from the typical hotel buffet or standard holiday breakfast.

I opted for the Power Breakfast, which featured a delicious bagel accompanied by a small continental selection of cheese and sliced meat. This meal also included coffee and juice. My son thoroughly enjoyed his smoked salmon and cream cheese bagel, a favourite of his so it was clearly well executed.

The coffee was as good as you would hope in a place dedicated to beans as well as bagels! I had a cappuccino, which was perfectly served and presented. The flavour profile was rich and satisfying.

The staff were professional and friendly, offering great recommendations and engaging in pleasant conversation. Their attentiveness and warmth added to the overall positive experience.

Overall, this cafe provided a memorable start to our day with its great food, lovely atmosphere, and excellent service. Highly recommended!","published_at":"7 months name: iBoenda
description:
Ontdek de authentieke smaak van Indonesie bij iBoenda. Met liefde bereid door een Indonesische moeder, bieden wij verse, huisgemaakte maaltijden vol rijke, traditionele smaken. Laat je verrassen door onze uitgebreide cateringopties en afhaalmaaltijden die de echte Indonesische keuken naar je tafel brengen. Proef de passie, proef de liefde!
Discover the authentic taste of Indonesia at iBoenda. Lovingly prepared by an Indonesian mother, we offer fresh, homemade meals full of rich, traditional flavors. Be surprised by our extensive catering options and takeaway dishes that bring the true Indonesian cuisine to your table. Taste the passion, taste the love!

First up, I tried the Gado-Gado, a delightful mix of veggies with peanut sauce. The dish included cabbage, green beans, and eggs, all topped with a rich and thick peanut sauce that provided a wonderful peanut flavor. The vegetables were perfectly boiled, adding a satisfying texture to the dish.
Next, I sampled the Nasi Campur, a traditional Indonesian dish. This platter had an assortment of items including rendang and vegetables. The rendang, one of Indonesia's national dishes, was absolutely delicious. Its rich and complex flavors complemented the fried rice perfectly.
Overall, Iboenda impressed me with its authentic flavors and high-quality ingredients. If you're in Amsterdam and craving Indonesian cuisine, I highly recommend giving Iboenda a try. The woman highly recommended eating at iBoenda as she said the food was the best Indonesian restaurant in the Netherlands in her opinion. Well, this woman was not wrong. It is little paradise in my opinion! You will never get an authentic, traditional and fantastic home cooked cuisine anywhere in the world as good as this restaurant! I've eaten in Indonesia too...I'm not exaggerating. They also do take aways and an equivalent to 'Just Eat'. I ate in the restaurant twice it was that good. I just wanted to try a little bit of everything. It's like a buffet style counter where you can choose whatever you like, honestly it's amazing and the restaurant is clean. I am only in Amsterdam for a few days but I guarantee, I will be visiting iBoenda a second and hopefully a third time again before I leave. I hope my mum won't ever get to read this as she doesn't use the internet, but as much as I love her Indonesian cooking, this Indonesian restaurant is far better and that is saying something, because I love my mum's cooking. If you miss Indonesian food, or whether you have never tried it, I absolutely recommend you eat in and get a take away too as you will not be disappointed with the food and price. Seriously, my mouth is watering just thinking about it! Thank you to the lady on the train that recommended this restaurant/take away. I will make sure when I next visit Amsterdam, one of the first places to come will be iBoenda. name: Restaurant Bar Kantoor
description: Bar Kantoor is the nicest office in Amsterdam, also open after office hours! ;) With our monumental building and sun-drenched terrace in the middle of the green Westerpark, we are a real eye-catcher. We are a 100% vegetarian restaurant. Come and enjoy the most delicious breakfasts, sandwiches, Meze to share and surprising cocktails.

The dishes arrived with perfect timing and while waiting we could enjoy the office-inspired yet comfy landscape. When someone wanted to order a bottle of wine, the waiter kindly offered a second menu. The concept of shared dishes also really worked well for a larger group where you have different preferences.

The fusian food was overall of good quality for what we paid. A personal favourite was the Japanse pancake. On the flip side, a dish that could easily improve was the pavlova where the mango ice cream was too sweet and should be replaced with a more neutral and soft flavour like vanilla. After another 15 minutes of waiting, I had to go inside to get the menu myself. Despite being there for 35 minutes, no one came to take our order, so we had to walk up to the staff.

When we finally ordered a bottle of wine, we were told it would be at least a 20-minute wait. For a bottle of wine, this seemed excessive. 20 minutes later, we were told the wine we ordered wasn't available, so we picked another one. Another 10 minutes passed, and they returned to tell us the wine wasn't cold. They asked if we wanted to drink it warm. Seriously?

At this point, we just asked for any cold white wine that wouldn't take another 20 minutes to arrive. After yet another wait, they finally brought it.

Whether you're looking for hearty meals or light bites, our menu has something for everyone. Enhance your dining experience by pairing your meal with our carefully selected artisanal beers and natural wines. Our cafe features a warm and inviting atmosphere that welcomes all. If you're hunting for a vegan-friendly spot in Amsterdam, look no further--SOIL is the perfect place to indulge in vibrant, plant-based cuisine!

name: Restaurant Black
description: Discover the culinary gem that is Restaurant Black, nestled in the vibrant heart of Amsterdam city center. Serving the best breakfast, lunch, and dinner near you, it's a must-visit spot for food-lovers. Looking for the best steak in Amsterdam? Your search ends at the doors of Restaurant Black. We also specialize in fine dining, offering an exquisite Lobster experience that will tantalize your taste buds. Located in the bustling Leidseplein, we're not just another restaurant - we're the best restaurant in Amsterdam. So whether you're craving a hearty breakfast, a leisurely lunch, or a decadent dinner, Restaurant Black has got you covered.

name: taqueria lima west
description:
Crazy good Mexican food. A whole lot of tacos, burritos, bowls and snacks, Taqueria LIMA has got it all!
Our chefs serve you the best classics like the taco Al Pastor, homemade braised beef or pulled chicken. But also a great Vegan Jack Fruit taco.
Come taste our light, fresh and easy going Mexican street food. El Super Taco Loco!

featured_reviews:
[{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNQcnV6aFNBEAE","rating":5,"name":"Ziwen Qi","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111587346369105638085?hl=en-GB","review_text":"The chicken available here is an absolute steal. Compared to other leading supermarkets, it is much more reasonably priced. Yet, the price tag in no way reflects a compromise on quality. Each piece of chicken looks and feels fresh. The flesh has a healthy color and a firm texture, a clear indication of its freshness. Whether you're planning to make a roasted chicken for a family dinner or a chicken salad for a light lunch, you can be sure that the chicken from this supermarket will work wonders in your kitchen.

Moreover, it's not just the chicken. The entire range of products in the supermarket adheres to the principle of "high quality at a low cost". You can find fresh produce, pantry staples, and even luxury items at prices that will put a smile on your face. The produce section is filled with a colorful array of fruits and vegetables, all of which look as if they were freshly picked from the farm.

The staff at this supermarket are also worth mentioning. They are always available to assist customers, whether it's answering questions about products or helping to carry heavy bags to your car. A good amount of places had kitchens closing for 830pm and couldn't accommodate us.

Toussaint was able to get us considering the late seating. The staff is courteous and attentive. The main room is small but warm and charming. We had a couple beers to start an Texel Skuumkoppe a delicious Affligem Blond beer both served perfectly.

For dinner we had the Chicken Special for the night which was a roasted chicken w lemon as seasoning , with side of potatoes and carrots. We also had the Sausage dinner w mashed potatoes and vegetables. Both dinners were good portions, but most importantly well prepared and seasoned and you can tell that the dishes were fresh and made to order.

For dessert we had the apple pie w ice cream and whipped cream and a slice of carrot cake. Both deserts were well made without any over sweetness and they hit the spot perfectly.

Overall highly recommend this place for a quick lunch or casual dinner. Solid value for the food. Atmosphere is calm and quaint and very cute. name: Meo's Colosseum | Surinamese Restaurant in Amsterdam
description:
Meo's Colosseum is an authentic Surinamese restaurant located in the heart of Amsterdam, offering a unique fusion of African, Asian, and European flavors that reflect the rich culinary traditions of Suriname.
Whether you're in the mood for a hearty Roti, flavorful Pom, or spicy Bami, our menu has something for everyone.
We pride ourselves on using fresh, locally-sourced ingredients to create dishes that are both delicious and full of heritage. With a warm and inviting atmosphere, Meo's Colosseum is perfect for casual dining, takeout, or private events.

Join us to experience the best of Surinamese cuisine right here in Amsterdam!

This is not a fully vegan restaurant, but it has vegetarian/vegan options. And the authentic Surinamese flavours still come forward amazingly. It's really an old-Dutch cafe type of vibe in terms of building style and wooden bar etc. But there are a lot of African and Caribbean elements woven into the decoration and interior. An interesting place to say the least. They have a beautiful community based collaboration going on with another Surinamese clothing brand: Patta!

What did we taste?

Drinks:
Ginger Beer
Markoesa drink

-- Both intense and sweet! Which is something you'll mostly get at a Surinamese place. Eze and I both have a sweet tooth so this satisfied us amazingly. The Ginger Beer was authentically made following a Surinamese recipe. The Markoesa drink is like a passion fruit lemonade. One of my favourite things ever to drink, so I was a happy girl!

Appetizers:
Breaded fried plantain with peanut sauce (Bakabana)
Cassava fries with salted shredded cod fish (Telo Bakkeljauw)
Home made fries (which they gave us extra!)

-- Classics! Probably the best bakabana I've tried till date. Very nice and crispy on the outside, and soft on the inside. And not too greasy as well. Peanut stew was delicious, and I'm picky when it comes to that. The Telo Bakkeljauw was really nice too and a bit of a surprise. I've tasted many different versions of bakkeljauw but this one seemed a little less sweet than I'm used to and also more fresh. So less artificial flavor enhancers (big fan of that)! The Telo becomes a bit dry when you leave it to cool for too long, but that's just how it works with fried cassava. The potato fries were simply amazing with a nice mayo to accompany it.

Mains:
Surinamese authentic noodles (Bami, vegan)
Vegan Roti

-- Both really amazing. Eze hasn't tasted much Surinamese cuisine before and therefore went on quite an adventure. I'm not new to the kitchen however but the flavors were really authentic and great, even with the vegan versions. Then you know what's up. They know how to cook here and you feel the love being put in the dishes. We loved it and the portions are large!

We literally didn't get to desserts because we were stuffed lol.

Meo's Colosseum, thanks so much for your hospitality and love. May many more people come to invest in this black-owned authentic place in one of the hearts of Amsterdam (Oud-West). Shirley is such a warm person with a beautiful vision and she deserves all the support she can get!

name: KFC
description: Nergens smaakt kip zo lekker als bij KFC. De reden daarvoor is het unieke, geheime recept van Colonel Harland Sanders. Al in 1939 slaagde hij erin het geheime mengsel van 11 kruiden en specerijen samen te stellen. Hiermee blijft het kippenvlees binnenin sappig en zacht terwijl het buiten een lekker knapperig korstje krijgt.

So we went there to get the food. Order everything again at the digital register and wait. And wait some more. After 20 minutes we hear our number being called out, someone who muttered something that didn't sound like the order went right, and seeing them flee to the back of the kitchen to avoid us. The other personnel was standing around doing nothing, claiming they could not help us because it wasn't their order. About 4 staff members kept trying to dodge us by heading into the kitchen or just staring and say nothing.

Eventually someone found a bag with three of our 12 ordered items an then some action slowly started going on. One person slowly tried to gather the rest of the missing items, starting off with the milkshakes (why someone would choose the one thing that can melt over time still puzzles me).

[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURUbnFMaXlBRRAB","rating":5,"name":"Muhammad Awais","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115511631093729387264?hl=en-GB","review_text":""Wow, what an incredible dining experience! The flavors and aromas transported me straight to Istanbul! The service was warm and attentive, and the atmosphere was cozy and inviting. name: Raina Indian Restaurant
description:
Welcome to Raina Indian Restaurant, an exquisite culinary venture in Amsterdam founded by Suresh Raina, the star cricketer of India. With a passion for both cricket and cooking, Suresh Raina envisioned a restaurant that would bring the best of Indian flavors from different regions to the world.
At Raina Indian Restaurant, we invite you to embark on a gastronomic journey where authenticity and taste reign supreme. Our menu showcases a handpicked selection of dishes inspired by the rich culinary heritage of India. From North to South, East to West, each plate tells a unique story, transporting your taste buds to the vibrant streets of India.

The desert, was good taste, but they put too much salt on it. It would be better smaller flakes.

The bill was the same of any top restaurant of Amsterdam, but with definitely one of the worst food.

First and foremost, I want to extend my sincere gratitude for taking the time to write a review.

I personally have worked with our team to thoroughly investigate the incident and have implemented necessary measures to prevent its recurrence in the future. Our ultimate goal is to consistently deliver exceptional dining experiences, and we regret not meeting your expectations on this occasion.
Once again, I apologize for any inconvenience caused and for the negative impact it had on your visit. If you decide to give us another chance, please feel free to contact me directly via email at fboffice@deleurope.com so that we can ensure your next visit to Trattoria Graziella exceeds all expectations.

Kind regards,

The ambiance inside was really nice--cozy, with just the right amount of lighting, which made the whole place feel warm and inviting. It was also clean, which is always a good thing. Plus, they had air conditioning, which was a lifesaver in this crazy hot weather.

The staff were super friendly. They were always ready to help, and their positive attitudes really added to the experience. The owner, on the other hand, seemed a bit stressed out, which threw off the vibe a little, but hey, everyone has their off days, so I won't let that affect my overall impression too much.

Now, onto the food. The dishes were served in smaller portions, which I actually loved because it let me try a bunch of different things. I'm not super familiar with Spanish cuisine, so this was a fun way to get a taste of it. I don't eat pork, so I had to skip a few items, but everything I did try was absolutely delicious.

I'll definitely be coming back, and I'm already thinking about bringing some friends along next time. Mamas & Tapas is a solid spot if you're looking for tasty food in a relaxed, comfortable setting. name: Volare
description: Een trattoria in Amsterdam-West, jouw favoriete hangout. Schuif aan met familie en vrienden voor een heerlijke lunch met homemade focaccia's of antipasti, pasta en pizza's van onze pizzaiolo waarbij een Italiaanse fles wijn uiteraard niet mag ontbreken.

The starters were fast, calamari was super good. But the waiter took it away even though we were still eating. Then two of the pastas my friend ordered were served cold, so they asked for new ones. They got new ones after the rest of us finished our food and it was apparently too cheesy although it was a truffle pasta. Two other friends' pastas were also too salty. I ordered a pizza with anchovies and even without the anchovies it was way too salty. It didn't feel authentic but the restaurant interior was very beautiful and spacious. It's nice for pictures but for food I would not really recommend. There were these frat boys who came with a big group and were being a complete menace. They were super loud, rude, and disrespectful. Everyone in the restaurant was uncomfortable. They would yell and swear, sing songs without being mindful of other customers. Some of them even threw up on the table which instantly made some of us lose our appetite. I wish someone would have told them to quiet down. name: Osteria Bella Ciao Oud-West
description:
Your local Italian Osteria that's all about having good food with a drink or two (or more) with your partner, family and friends.

Located in the two most iconic neighborhoods in Amsterdam, Osteria Bella Ciao it's your authentic modern Osteria with a focus on seasonal and organic italian ingredients.

Our talented Italian chefs are all about delivering a mix of traditional and contemporary dishes respecting each ingredient as our Mamma would do, all served along great and delicious Aperitifs, Italian-Inspired cocktails and of course wines.

Reservations are appreciated but of course walk-ins are more than welcome.

Larger group? Send us and enquire to discover our preset-menus and availability.

The food was incredible--each dish was thoughtfully prepared and bursting with flavor. The staff was not only warm and welcoming but also incredibly knowledgeable, sharing insights about the menu and the city. They even gave me a list of restaurants to try while I'm here, which was such a thoughtful touch.

name: MOGU Malatang
description: Make your perfect Malatang bowl! We've got about 50 fresh items to choose from. The chef will cut them to bitesize and makes sure everything is cooking the right amount of time in one of our signature broths: Sichuan, Miso or Tom Kha. All our broths are vegan and made from scratch in-house! Super delicious, customized, healthy food for around 17 euro for a huge bowl. We're the first and currently only malatang place in Amsterdam!

Went to Mogu last Sept 6, 2024, and had the savoury Japanese miso soup which I find it super comforting especially during the rainy/cold season.

An offerings of Clean, MSG Free and the most freshest ingredients you can find serve in a bowl of warm and extremely delicious soup of your choice which is very rare with the restaurants nowadays.

The Concept of the restaurant was explained in a brief yet detailed way to fully maximize the malatang experience.
Mogo can be considered as a destination that one can has to cross out when in Amsterdam, or when in the Netherlands.
Definitely worth a visit, it may be my first time trying it but definitely will not be the last.

See you very soon!

If you're in Amsterdam and craving some vegetarian comfort food, Mogu Malatang is the place to be. Nestled in the heart of the city, this cozy eatery offers a delightful blend of Chinese Sichuan, Japanese miso, and Thai tom yum soup bases that will tantalize your taste buds.

One of the standout features of Mogu Malatang is the variety of vegetarian options available. You can choose from an array of fresh vegetables, assorted mushrooms, tofu, and different types of eggs to customize your noodle and soup combo. Each bowl is a flavorful journey, with the rich, aromatic broths perfectly complementing the wholesome ingredients.

For instance, my dish weighed in at about 380 grams and cost close to 16 euros, which is quite reasonable considering the quality and portion size. The staff also gave our complimentary edamame later on in the evening and I thought that was a very nice gesture.

The ambiance at Mogu Malatang is equally appealing. Whether you prefer indoor or outdoor seating, the restaurant provides a comfortable and welcoming atmosphere. The indoor area is cozy and perfect for a quiet meal, while the outdoor seating offers a pleasant experience, especially on a cool day.

What sets Mogu Malatang apart is the service. The staff are incredibly friendly and attentive, always ready to help you navigate the menu and ensure you have a great dining experience. Their warm hospitality adds a personal touch that makes your visit even more enjoyable.

In summary, Mogu Malatang is a fantastic spot for anyone looking to indulge in delicious vegetarian noodles and soups. The only thing I wish was that it would have more variety to choose from, and that they would have some sauces available (like those in Asia) but other than that, it's a must-visit for comfort food lovers in Amsterdam.","published_at":"7 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-05-26T07:51:46","response_from_owner_text":"Thank you for your lovely review ","response_from_owner_ago":"7 months ago","response_from_owner_date":"2024-05-26T11:37:00","review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNgh8ZoFwOfH_oBiGzkjPrqj1l8ph9eevfaUSyV=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipP3ErzghS1fMPjw2tclV2pXKL1a5cQbAW05aYH4=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMmBZEE-pWcE69yY-mMIpFy5y_tqt-383261P4Q=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNoTyffitSNCxE3MGfE9DsUdeko6GxazuPhk9wh=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipM6bTnBGn_oQr5QzjPR3D92N-f8iC1JMpgbw3ww=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipPiL_JsrQUo1mGrnpPHAPqV3znXWg2DeFz91XtH=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipP_0gd3lXwyQwDM58Fd5a161z-IrF5TLtG4sYXp=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNzq3Zo6ZqoH3JUQW497hEDQfxP7Z48QaE2jvQx=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMLvN44BBHd31vHNMlF5ipT2LhdoFg2Of1qhvqg=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNdc0H3KLYXbRukuYcSC7TyeJheu7PVd61YuuSu=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOPX_ucgs5cf3HfsTr5DdmCz6xw_mLB-ydME-N6=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOMO0UUdaZqqFwp9SCGF1ajPoU0Dx7_rylNXPV_=s1024"]},{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURQal91d1RnEAE","rating":4,"name":"sam williams","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114306184556497888166?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Loved the concept of choosing your food and all the plant based foods. name: Sorel's Bar and Lounge
description:
Sorel's Bar and Lounge is widely recognized as one of the most celebrated bourbon bars in Amsterdam. We are well known for our local partnerships, specialty cocktails and showcasing spirits from the best distilleries in the Netherlands.
Sorel's Bar and Lounge serves specialty cocktails, as well as burgers, sandwiches and local dishes with a unique 'bourbonized' twist. The bar is a great place to unwind after a long day.

The cocktails here are thoughtfully crafted, and the focus on quality ingredients makes a real difference. I love that they highlight Dutch elements without overdoing it; it feels authentic, not gimmicky. The ambiance strikes a great balance, too: it's stylish yet unpretentious, making it a comfortable place to sit back and relax, whether you're out with friends or just stopping by on your own for business.

Service-wise, they're efficient and friendly, which adds to the whole experience. Plus, the bartenders know their stuff and are genuinely enthusiastic, which makes for a nice interaction when ordering. All in all, I'd say Sorel's is one of those bars that's ideal for a memorable night out--cool enough for a special occasion but relaxed enough to visit anytime. [{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUQ3aVl5cEF3EAE","rating":5,"name":"Anthony Leigh Dunstan","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109761061689066249816?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Braai

Had a hankering for ribs when organising a mate's night out in Amsterdam. It'd been 2 years since I'd been out in the city and I wanted somewhere reminiscent of the days before migration.

Braai did not disappoint.. at all! In fact I'm surprised they're not on trip advisor's top 20 list of Amsterdam ribs' establishments. They should be. Some of the best ribs I've ever had - better than Cafe de Klos which were #5 on trip advisor's list. Tender without falling apart with an awesome BBQ sauce as glaze and dipping. Topped with caramelised onions was an awesome touch. There was a smokiness other places hadn't achieved. I'm pretty sure they used a Texas smoker as advertised on older menus.

My mate had the pork belly which to my taste was delightfully fatty and sweet with a gentle smokiness. I had just one bite so can't say much more.

The service was immediately friendly and welcoming. The server came by regularly but didn't crowd us. My mate took care of the bill (he's a keeper) and I'm hoping he tipped her. She was great!

Being off alcohol I was very glad to sample two zero percenters they had from boutique breweries - an ipa from... somewhere in the Netherlands; and Oedipus' "Dorinku" Japanese inspired citrus beer. Twas a gooden.

A great feed and a chill atmosphere 2 mins from Westerpark.

Highly recommend if you love a South African Braai (bbq).","published_at":"4 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-08-25T14:02:07","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipM0KGfIQFULRdBlMZkOsGsrc6y9WhOjqeJslk1Q=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipPYuiE9zpZq7uivsBJYhpHATvdBPNux_jeRVSoK=s1024"]},{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUMzcjVHREhREAE","rating":5,"name":"Mac Birrell (Maccles)","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117166974542005752344?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Tucked away in Westerpark, I highly recommend this restaurant for the lovely service and hearty, yummy food. *	The carpaccio was unappetizing and barely resembled a proper dish. It was also frozen.
*	The tagliatelle with lobster was another disappointment--the lobster was empty, leaving only pasta in tomato sauce.
*	For the mains, the beef, requested well-done, was served raw, and the salmon was excessively oily and tasteless. My wife even felt unwell after trying it.
*	By the time dessert arrived at 11:45 PM, our appetite and patience were gone.

The waitress, clearly sympathetic, acknowledged our concerns and called the manager. He apologized and assured us of a full refund. However, we later received a call offering only half the amount as vouchers for the same restaurant--a poor resolution, especially as we live in Germany and are unlikely to return. When we spoke to the owner, she became defensive and unfriendly when we mentioned sharing this review.

To make matters worse, other guests around us voiced similar complaints about the service and food quality. It was clear that this wasn't an isolated incident.

This experience was unacceptable. Instead of celebrating New Year's Eve in a joyful and memorable way, we ended up hungry and disheartened on the streets of Amsterdam. name: Spaghetteria
description: Bent u op zoek naar een uitstekend restaurant in Amsterdam? Verwen uw smaakpapillen bij Spaghetteria, een van de beste eetgelegenheden in Amsterdam. Als een lokale favoriet, biedt Spaghetteria een authentieke en onvergetelijke culinaire ervaring. Of u nu een echte foodie bent, op zoek bent naar een plek voor fijn dineren of gewoon wilt genieten van traditioneel Nederlands eten, Spaghetteria is de place to be. Onze Amsterdamse hotspot is bekend om het serveren van de meest verrukkelijke pasta's en is een must-visit voor elke culinaire liefhebber. Ontdek waarom we worden beschouwd als een van de top Amsterdamse restaurants. Proef de heerlijke smaken van Spaghetteria vandaag nog!

name: Chez Nina Green Brasserie
description:
Chez Nina Green Brasserie is het vegetarische restaurant waar de Zweedse chef en beroemde kookboeken schrijfster Nina Olsson en haar team van ontbijt tot en met diner verrassende vegetarische gerechten serveren in combinatie met huisgemaakte limonades, cocktails, natuur en bio wijnen.
At Chez Nina Green Brasserie we serve delicious and fresh vegetarian dishes (with vegan options) for breakfast, lunch and dinner and every moment in between, all created by Nina Olsson. Next to the dishes we serve organic coffee, tea, home made limonades and a wide selection of natural as well as classical wines. And we also invite you to try out our selection of homemade cocktails (also 0% ones) and organic beers.
address: Van Limburg Stirumplein 10 A, 1051 BE Amsterdam
featured_question: {"question":"Can I bring my dog? ","answer":"hi Agnesa, thanks for asking. When you make a reservation on our terrace you can bring your dog under the condition that your dog has ' restaurant experience' and will not bother other guests. Inside the restaurant we have very little space, so there we recommend not to bring your dog. Hope this information is helpful to you and looking forward to see you at Chez Nina soon.  Warm regards, Team Chez Nina. name: Orontes West - Turks Restaurant Amsterdam - Mediterraans Restaurant Amsterdam
description:
Turks restaurant Amsterdam voor lunch en diner.

Wilt u genieten van de Mediterraans/Turkse keuken, dan verwelkomen we u graag in ons Turks restaurant in Amsterdam! Restaurant Orontes West bevindt zich op het Hugo de Grootplein, wat slechts vijf minuten lopen van de Jordaan is. Middenin onze hoofdstad kan u genieten van het beste dat de Mediterraans/Turkse keuken te bieden heeft!

The mozzarella on the Margharita as well as the buffalo mozzarella and Parmesan on the Oro de Buffala were so rich in flavor that nothing, absolutely nothing was missing. The homemade chili oil is very tasty as well and goes perfectly with the fluffy pizza dough.
The dessert menu is very straightforward with just two dishes, but it has a lot to offer. Both the tiramisu and the sweet foccacia are highly recommended. 
Reservations in advance are recommended. We have now made two reservations at relatively short notice, both a few days beforehand, due to cancellations, you just have to stay on it and see if any slots open up.
For me, it's a must-try in Amsterdam, nothing comes close in terms of pizza.
